# Dashboard modal sizing

Admin dashboard modals and sheets should feel spacious — not the compact `max-w-sm` / `max-w-md` used in the consumer app.

## Defaults

Use shared constants from `@/components/dashboard/dashboard-ui`:

- **`DASHBOARD_MODAL_CONTENT_CLASS`** — forms and single-column flows (`max-w-2xl`, `p-8`)
- **`DASHBOARD_MODAL_LARGE_CLASS`** — wide workflows like broadcast composer (`max-w-6xl`)
- **`DashboardModal`** — wrapper for new dashboard dialogs; pass `size="large"` only when needed

## Do

```tsx
import { DashboardModal, DASHBOARD_MODAL_CONTENT_CLASS } from "@/components/dashboard/dashboard-ui";

<DashboardModal open={open} onOpenChange={setOpen} title="New community">
  {/* form */}
</DashboardModal>

<ResponsiveSheet modalClassName={DASHBOARD_MODAL_CONTENT_CLASS} ... />
```

## Don't

- Use `max-w-sm`, `max-w-md`, or `max-w-lg` for dashboard modals
- Build raw `ModalContent` without the dashboard size classes
- Reuse consumer-app modal sizing in `/dashboard` routes

## Minimum widths

| Use case | Width |
|----------|-------|
| Create / invite / settings forms | `max-w-2xl` |
| Milestone verify / reject | `max-w-2xl` |
| Broadcast / multi-panel composer | `max-w-6xl` |

## Auth pages

Sign-in and accept-invite use **`DashboardAuthCard`** (`max-w-2xl`, `p-8`/`p-10`) — same spacious sizing, no logo badge.
